to make sure all chages are uploaded since last commit. probably was about ui
user feature enabled, templates for it have been created. article-tags m2m field moved to TagsRecord model, to save who saved it

two net items added to TODO. basic user features of django implemented. login, logout, password change, user profile templates have been added. TagRecord model created, as intermediary model between Tag and Article2.
ui improvement on header. hamburger icon fixed.
Turkish categories fix, it was showing all the tags.
build failed due to a static file (/images/remove_icon.svg). installed and configured whitenoise because of this
the issue was actually icon file was not added to git add properly, since it copy pasted through Explorer. Added it to commit.

this commit includes the featuring of redis. It was implemented for plotly, but it is still going on. Also, the project team delivered some feedback on creation of an integer field, which they and you could utilize it how many times a TagRecord selection should be counted, how many journalists are jailed, things like that. Some ui improvements, TaggingForm established in a form. Since you accept an integer to be saved with a tag, limit of numbers per selection is limited to one. But there is no default option for that since tags field is an M2M one, you passed MaxSelectionLenth attribute to TaggingForm.
